# The vendored upstream scenario (product.liquid, product.mustache, blogpost.liquid) and the Heddle
# entry's template (product.heddle) are byte-significant: their raw newlines flow into rendered
# output and into the parity comparison. Pin everything under this fallback to LF so a Windows
# checkout cannot smudge it to CRLF and diverge from the LF bytes vendored/rendered on CI.
* text eol=lf
